['\n<p>\n\t<strong>Welcome to Howth</strong></p>\n<p>\n\tSo that you get the best experience as a visiting support boat (or &ldquo;Support Person Vessel&rdquo; as the Racing Rules of Sailing refer to you as!), the following few notes are important for you to read.</p>\n<p>\n\t<strong>Registration</strong></p>\n<p>\n\tIt is mandatory for Support Person Vessels to be registered for this event. You can do this when you are registering the competitor&#39;s boat. You will be given a numbered flag which you must display throughout the event. There is a refundable deposit of &euro;20.00 for each flag.</p>\n<p>\n\t<a href="https://hyc.ie/iodai-national-chamionships-2024-registration"><span style="color:#0000ff;"><strong>Click here for the Registration location.</strong></span></a></p>\n<p>\n\t<strong>Launching</strong></p>\n<p>\n\tPlease use the public slipway, beside the Lifeboat House, per the image below.</p>\n<p>\n\tThe HYC slipway is for the sailors and for official RIBs (Safety, marks, jury, etc.).</p>\n<p>\n\t<img alt="" src="data:image/png;base64," /></p>\n<p>\n\t<strong>RIB Berthing</strong></p>\n<p>\n\tIn advance of your arrival, please make contact with the HYC Marina Office (+353 1 8392 777) to be allocated a berth. You may NOT berth on the pontoons under the cranes or by the slipway. Those spaces are for official RIBs only.</p>\n<p>\n\tWhen you return from the race area each day, please berth in your allocated space.</p>\n<p>\n\t<strong>Car and trailer parking</strong></p>\n<p>\n\tParking is free in Howth Harbour and around Howth. There are no pay-parking areas to worry about.</p>\n<p>\n\tIt is vitally important that you respect the yellow boxes in the harbour area. They are for emergency services access and they are guarded by the Harbour Master and his team. You will get a hefty fine if you break the parking regulations.</p>\n<p>\n\t<strong>Trailer storage</strong></p>\n<p>\n\t<a href="https://hyc.ie/iodai-national-chamionships-2024-trailers"><span style="color:#0000ff;"><strong>Click here for trailer storage</strong></span></a></p>\n<p>\n\t<strong>Fuel</strong></p>\n<p>\n\tCome to Marina office for instructions. &nbsp;Owners must supply their own petrol cans. Payment can be made in cash (Euro) or by card.</p>\n']
